Scenario: Student Grading System using if-else if in C
Scenario Explanation:
A student gets grades based on their marks:

90 - 100 → Grade A

80 - 89 → Grade B

70 - 79 → Grade C

60 - 69 → Grade D

Below 60 → Grade F (Fail)
Scenario: Traffic Light System using if-else if in C
Scenario Explanation:
A traffic light has three signals:

Red Light → STOP

Yellow Light → READY to go

Green Light → GO
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    char light;

    // Taking input from the user
    printf("Enter traffic light color (R for Red, Y for Yellow, G for Green): ");
    scanf(" %c", &light);

    // Traffic signal logic using if-else if
    if (light == 'R' || light == 'r') {
        printf("Signal: RED - STOP!\n");
    } else if (light == 'Y' || light == 'y') {
        printf("Signal: YELLOW - Get READY to go!\n");
    } else if (light == 'G' || light == 'g') {
        printf("Signal: GREEN - GO!\n");
    } else {
        printf("Invalid input! Please enter R, Y, or G.\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
